<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857En3/4</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-29">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1916, noon</hi>
                                    </date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2859. Department’s March 28, 4 p. m. <hi rend="italic">Englishman</hi>. Department now has affidavit of American
                                citizen stating that <hi rend="italic">Englishman</hi> was sunk by
                                German submarine <hi rend="italic">U–19</hi> which he saw. Please
                                add this to your previous statement to the Foreign Office in regard
                                to the steamer <hi rend="italic">Englishman</hi>.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>